  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.13.0\n\n### What happened?\n\n```\r\nðŸ¤£  hardhat-foundry-template git:(master) ðŸŒ¹ npx hardhat test                                                                                                             \r\nError in plugin hardhat-foundry: User-configured sources path (./src) doesn't match path configured in foundry (src)\r\n\r\nFor more info run Hardhat with --show-stack-traces\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n`foundry.toml`\r\n\r\n```\r\n[default]\r\nsrc = 'src'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['lib']\r\n```\r\n\r\n`hardhat.config.ts`\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst config: HardhatUserConfig = {\r\n  solidity: {\r\n    version: \"0.8.13\",\r\n    settings: {\r\n      optimizer: {\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n        runs: 200,\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n  paths: {\r\n    sources: \"./src\", // Use ./src rather than ./contracts as Hardhat expects\r\n    cache: \"./cache_hardhat\", // Use a different cache for Hardhat than Foundry\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nread the source code and find that there is a logic error(the condition should be two paths, not two strings):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/57c56d2353da8828d6b2c167b24bd70b6298a8cc/packages/hardhat-foundry/src/index.ts#L59\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\nhardhat-foundry",
